  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Evidence carries explicitly low confidence (~50%) across multiple factors, honestly documented with appropriate rationale and wide uncertainty bounds. Despite low confidence, all credibility factor achieved levels meet or exceed required levels, provenance is complete, and the decision record clearly articulates the basis for acceptance with full acknowledgement of residual uncertainty. This is a structurally clean package; no weakener should fire.",
