      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) are documented in the FDA Critical Path report. Experimental temperature held at 37°C ±0.5°C, hematocrit 33% ±2%. Confidence in test condition fidelity ~55%; exact impeller tip clearance in experimental rig is not reported, introducing geometric uncertainty. This gap is explicitly flagged and bounded via sensitivity analysis showing <5% NIH sensitivity to ±50µm clearance variation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
