      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, hemolysis exponents C and alpha, inlet velocity profiles) are documented with sources and uncertainty distributions. Monte Carlo UQ propagates input uncertainty to NIH output. Confidence in input distributions ~50%; hemolysis power-law exponents C and alpha are drawn from a meta-analysis of n=12 published datasets with high inter-study variability (CV ~30%). This low confidence is explicitly documented and the wide output uncertainty bounds reflect it. Level 3 achieved via comprehensive UQ documentation."
    },
